Node.Notes: Means "good insight/understanding"; some extend meaning to "success/behavior"; others correct the text with "name/repute" to fit with the preceding conjoined element, "favor."
Figuratively, "he will make your path level"; non-figuratively "he will direct your life."
This verse states the consequence of following the advice of v. 7, which is it leads to physical healing and soundness of body.

Some translations follow the variant reading of the Septuagint (LXX) "he punishes every son he accepts." Most interpret "he delights in" as a relative modifier to "son." The tree here represents "he delights in (his) son like a father."
Uncertain precious stone; preferences range from coral, pearl, to rubies. General term like 宝石 may be preferable.
Wisdom is pictured as a generous person with gifts in her hands offered to those who come to her.
The referents of "them," "sound judgment and discretion," are not given until the next clause. Many transpose the clause order for a smoother translation.
Seems to mean "to the ones who need it (i.e., the good you are able to do)."
